(PLANKAC TECHNICAL REPORT) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(ENGLISH) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(ABSTRACT) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(PlankaC is a substantial executable Plankalkuel-profile implementation in C.) Tj
T*
(It provides a parser, interpreter, typed IR, text bytecode, generated C,) Tj
T*
(generated x86-64 assembly, 8086/DOS-oriented assembly emission, embedding API,) Tj
T*
(host APIs for .plk applications, and a conformance corpus.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The project does not claim to be a complete historical reconstruction of) Tj
T*
(Plankalkuel. Its purpose is narrower and more testable: preserve a) Tj
T*
(source-oriented profile, make it executable, document the implemented) Tj
T*
(semantics, and expose compiler artifacts that can be checked by users.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(SOURCE BASIS) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The work is oriented around Konrad Zuse's published Plankalkuel material and) Tj
T*
(the later Plankalkuel 2000 implementation report. The bibliography is kept in) Tj
T*
(docs/bibliography.md. Those sources are used for notation, value-bank) Tj
T*
(terminology, plan/procedure structure, two-dimensional rows, structured) Tj
T*
(values, and the chess-modeling tradition.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The project intentionally separates source-derived language features from) Tj
T*
(modern extensions. The 3D geometry profile and graphical host procedures are) Tj
T*
(PlankaC extensions. They are useful, executable examples, not claims about the) Tj
T*
(documented historical core.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(ARCHITECTURE) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The repository is split into compiler and runtime layers:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(  * c/core: source loading, parser support, expression evaluation, runtime API;) Tj
T*
(  * c/types: marker parsing, type families, compatibility rules;) Tj
T*
(  * c/notation: linear and PAGE/table two-dimensional notation support;) Tj
T*
(  * c/analyzer: static checks and structural schema checks;) Tj
T*
(  * c/values: tagged values, bit packing, and fixed-point helpers;) Tj
T*
(  * c/ir: typed intermediate representation;) Tj
T*
(  * c/backends: bytecode, lowering report, generated C, x86-64 ASM, 8086 ASM;) Tj
T*
(  * c/models: chess board and game-state helpers;) Tj
T*
(  * c/targets: CLI, Windows GUI, Win16, and DOS hosts;) Tj
T*
(  * graphics/c: PlankaHost, PlankaGUI, PlankaCube, raster and export layers.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The practical compiler path is:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(.plk source -> parser/analyzer -> procedure table -> typed IR/bytecode ->) Tj
T*
(C/ASM/native runner) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(IMPLEMENTED PROFILE) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The implemented profile includes numbered procedures, V/C/Z/R value) Tj
T*
ET
